The paper deals with computational geometry and graph theory, specifically the problem of minimizing the area of rectangular layouts of contact graphs. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the NP-hardness of the problem, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper presents an infinite family of graphs that require a certain amount of area, which could be of interest to researchers in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
